Package: heeler
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, adduser
Description: lightweight, secure NTP server
 Heeler is a small, auditable NTPv4-compatible unicast time server for
 private networks, homelabs, and edge deployments. It serves the host
 system clock over UDP with conservative security defaults: loopback-only
 access, rate limiting, and no control or administration protocol.
 .
 Heeler serves the host system clock; it does not make an inaccurate host
 clock accurate, and it does not discipline the system clock.
